text: Holladay is a city in Salt Lake County, Utah, United States. It is part of the Salt Lake City, Utah Metropolitan Statistical Area. As of the 2020 census, 31,965 people lived in Holladay. This is up from 26,472 people at the 2010 census. It was reported in the 1990 census as the Holladay-Cottonwood CDP. ==References== ==Other websites== *Holladay official website Category:Cities in Utah
